706941f-a.title: Brooklyn: Surf Avenue - 5th Street (West)
706941f-a.text:
Surf Ave., south side, west from West 5th Street.
December 1923.
Fugene L. Armbruster Collection.

706942f-c.title: Brooklyn: Surf Avenue - 5th Street (West)
706942f-c.text:
(1)
Surf Ave., west from West 5th Street, showing at the right, (N.W.
corner of 5th Street), Vanderveer's Hotel.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
A closer view cf the afore mentioned hotel.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armkruster Collection.
(3)
A view, similar to No. 1.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellectiom.
(4)
another, aore of less similar, taken from a point farther westward
(Nest 6th Street).
Octoker 1928.
Eugene L. Amruster Collection.

706943f-b.title: Brooklyn: Surf Avenue - 5th Street (West)
706943f-b.text:
(1)
Surf Ave., north side, west of West 5th Street, showing in the fore-
ground, the car barns of the Manhattan Transit R.R. Co., and beyond it
the Brooklyn Edison Co's branch building. On the site of the car ter-
minal, once stood the Vanderveer Concourse Hotel, which was opened on
December 10, 1878. It was demoished in 1902.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, looking eastward.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
